♪ Now... ♪

00:02:06.751 --> 00:02:08.503 position:50% align:center
♪ Go and soar... ♪

00:02:08.586 --> 00:02:10.672 position:50% align:center
Whoa. That's dangerous.

00:02:10.755 --> 00:02:12.132 position:50% align:center
Is that Minami?

00:02:12.215 --> 00:02:14.592 position:50% align:center
What the heck is she
doing up there?

00:02:18.304 --> 00:02:19.514 position:50% align:center
[RANKA]
Speaking of Minami.

00:02:19.597 --> 00:02:21.057 position:50% align:center
[KANEISHI]
Oh, I've heard it, too!

00:02:21.141 --> 00:02:22.058 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
What?

00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:23.268 position:50% align:center
[RANKA]
Get this.

00:02:23.351 --> 00:02:25.812 position:50% align:center
Supposedly, she's stood
up a bunch of guys.

00:02:25.895 --> 00:02:28.189 position:50% align:center
[AWAKI]
Huh? She's that kinda girl?

00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:31.401 position:50% align:center
[RANKA] Maybe? She asks boys
out and then ghosts them.

00:02:31.484 --> 00:02:32.861 position:50% align:center
It's like she's got a
promise-breaking

00:02:32.944 --> 00:02:34.487 position:50% align:center
disorder or something.

00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:35.905 position:50% align:center
[AWAKI]
What the hell is that?

00:02:35.989 --> 00:02:38.533 position:50% align:center
[KANEISHI]
It's just a rumor.

00:02:38.616 --> 00:02:40.910 position:50% align:center
I can't picture her doing that.

00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:43.288 position:50% align:center
Wow, you're so
pure-hearted, Yomogi.

00:02:43.371 --> 00:02:45.123 position:50% align:center
C'mon, what's that mean?

00:02:56.176 --> 00:02:58.553 position:50% align:center
[MEI] Word's getting
out about you, Yume.

00:02:58.636 --> 00:03:00.930 position:50% align:center
--What do you mean?
--[camera snaps]

00:03:01.014 --> 00:03:02.807 position:50% align:center
[MEI] I heard you asked a
second-year to meet you

00:03:02.891 --> 00:03:04.684 position:50% align:center
and then you ditched
the poor sap.

00:03:04.768 --> 00:03:08.271 position:50% align:center
[YUME] Yeah. That guy totally
went off on me yesterday.

00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:11.858 position:50% align:center
[MEI] C'mon, girl. You know
that stuff gets around.

00:03:11.941 --> 00:03:12.859 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
Yeah.

00:03:12.942 --> 00:03:14.861 position:50% align:center
[MEI]
Look, I hate to say it,

00:03:14.944 --> 00:03:18.615 position:50% align:center
but don't you know the things
your class says about you?

00:03:18.698 --> 00:03:21.534 position:50% align:center
[YUME] You're not even in
my class, so why do you care?

00:03:21.618 --> 00:03:24.287 position:50% align:center
[MEI gasps] I've known
you forever, so sometimes

00:03:24.371 --> 00:03:27.332 position:50% align:center
I have to hit you with those
hard truths for your own good.

00:03:27.415 --> 00:03:29.668 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
Aw, thanks so much, Mom.

00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:30.752 position:50% align:center
[MEI scoffs]
Cut it out.

00:03:30.835 --> 00:03:31.670 position:50% align:center
[YUME giggles]

00:03:31.753 --> 00:03:33.296 position:50% align:center
[MEI chuckles]
Yume.

00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:35.924 position:50% align:center
Stop making promises
you won't keep.

00:03:38.802 --> 00:03:40.011 position:50% align:center
Hello?

00:03:42.263 --> 00:03:44.099 position:50% align:center
Fine.

00:03:44.182 --> 00:03:46.851 position:50% align:center
[ETHICS TEACHER] ...about the
different lines of thinking.

00:03:46.935 --> 00:03:51.147 position:50% align:center
There's Stoic Asceticism
and Epicurus' Hedonism.

00:03:51.231 --> 00:03:54.693 position:50% align:center
Now obviously, these things
contrast one another,

00:03:54.776 --> 00:03:55.902 position:50% align:center
so today we'll dis...

00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:57.320 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE TV HOST A ]
Basically, every year, 

00:03:57.404 --> 00:03:59.239 position:50% align:center
more and more tombs
are being dismantled.

00:03:59.322 --> 00:04:00.657 position:50% align:center
[MALE TV HOST A ]
Yes, it's true.

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:05.495 position:50% align:center
Huh... That reminds me,
isn't the memorial next week?

00:04:05.578 --> 00:04:08.581 position:50% align:center
[KOYOMI]
Huh...? Uh...

00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:10.375 position:50% align:center
Yeah, you're right.

00:04:10.458 --> 00:04:13.586 position:50% align:center
Well, have fun explaining to
everyone how you're unemployed.

00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:15.880 position:50% align:center
[KOYOMI]
Says the one who skips school.

00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:17.549 position:50% align:center
Hey, that's different.

00:04:17.632 --> 00:04:19.592 position:50% align:center
Besides, it's not like
anyone gave me the choice

00:04:19.676 --> 00:04:21.302 position:50% align:center
about going to
school or whatever.

00:04:21.386 --> 00:04:22.679 position:50% align:center
[MALE TV HOST B]
As strange as it sounds,

00:04:22.762 --> 00:04:24.514 position:50% align:center
this sort of thing is
becoming the new normal.

00:04:24.597 --> 00:04:26.850 position:50% align:center
How's it different?

00:04:26.933 --> 00:04:28.476 position:50% align:center
--[AWAKI] See ya.
--[NAZUMI] Bye.

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:29.769 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Later, guys.

00:04:34.149 --> 00:04:35.358 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Huh?

00:04:40.572 --> 00:04:41.781 position:50% align:center
[whimpers]

00:04:48.496 --> 00:04:49.497 position:50% align:center
Uh.

00:04:49.581 --> 00:04:51.916 position:50% align:center
[stomach growls]

00:04:54.586 --> 00:04:57.922 position:50% align:center
Hey there, do you need
help or something?

00:04:58.006 --> 00:04:59.632 position:50% align:center
I'm starving.

00:04:59.716 --> 00:05:00.508 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
What?

00:05:00.592 --> 00:05:03.595 position:50% align:center
Uh... Oh! Let's see.

00:05:05.388 --> 00:05:06.848 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
How's this?

00:05:06.931 --> 00:05:09.726 position:50% align:center
It's just leftovers from lunch,
but it's yours if you want it.

00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:17.108 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
I'll just leave you two alone.

00:05:19.319 --> 00:05:20.528 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:22.405 --> 00:05:24.741 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI whimpers]

00:05:24.824 --> 00:05:28.244 position:50% align:center
Thank you. You totally
just saved my life.

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:29.204 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Huh?

00:05:29.287 --> 00:05:30.914 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA]
I'm serious.

00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:34.000 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI] Uh, that's great.
Glad you're feeling better.

00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:36.002 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA]
What's your name, kid?

00:05:36.086 --> 00:05:37.003 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Huh?

00:05:37.087 --> 00:05:38.338 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA]
What's your name?!

00:05:38.421 --> 00:05:43.009 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI] My name?
Well, um, it's Yomogi Asanaka.

00:05:43.093 --> 00:05:46.137 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA]
Yomogi, huh...?

00:05:46.221 --> 00:05:48.181 position:50% align:center
That's a good name.

00:05:48.264 --> 00:05:50.100 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Thanks, I guess.

00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:53.770 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA] My name is Gauma.
I'm a kaiju user.

00:05:53.853 --> 00:05:56.022 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Kaiju? Yeah, sure.

00:05:56.106 --> 00:05:58.441 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA] And the reason
why I'm here is...

00:05:58.525 --> 00:06:00.527 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Can you just let me go, please?

00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:04.155 position:50% align:center
Thanks again. And I swear
I'll return the favor someday.

00:06:04.239 --> 00:06:08.201 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI] Uh. It's actually
fine if you don't!

00:06:08.284 --> 00:06:11.287 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA gasps]
Yomogi...

00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:16.376 position:50% align:center
[dog barks]

00:06:17.460 --> 00:06:19.921 position:50% align:center
Yomogi! We need to go.

00:06:20.005 --> 00:06:21.256 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
'Kay.

00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:23.258 position:50% align:center
We'll be back in a
little bit, Mother.

00:06:23.341 --> 00:06:24.467 position:50% align:center
Eh?

00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:26.970 position:50% align:center
I told you. We're having
dinner with Kamijo.

00:06:27.053 --> 00:06:28.888 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S GRANDMA grunts]

00:06:28.972 --> 00:06:30.640 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM]
Yomogi, I'm leaving!

00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:31.683 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S GRANDMA grunts]

00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:33.685 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI sighs]
You're so loud, Mom.

00:06:33.768 --> 00:06:34.978 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM]
You say something?

00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:36.813 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
I said you're loud.

00:06:38.606 --> 00:06:40.734 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM] And it's
good for the earth, too!

00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:43.653 position:50% align:center
[KAMIJO]
So, Yomogi, you're in...?

00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:44.904 position:50% align:center
I'm in high school.

00:06:44.988 --> 00:06:48.241 position:50% align:center
[KAMIJO] That's what I thought.
Which is why...

00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:50.660 position:50% align:center
Here. Congrats.

00:06:50.744 --> 00:06:52.537 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM]
What? My goodness!

00:06:52.620 --> 00:06:54.873 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you'll be going out
with your friends more now,

00:06:54.956 --> 00:06:56.416 position:50% align:center
so you'll need money.

00:06:56.499 --> 00:06:59.044 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM] How generous.
You didn't have to do that.

00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:00.795 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much.

00:07:00.879 --> 00:07:01.838 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM chuckles]

00:07:01.921 --> 00:07:03.131 position:50% align:center
[KAMIJO]
And it has a robot voice.

00:07:03.214 --> 00:07:05.675 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM laughs]

00:07:05.759 --> 00:07:08.511 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI'S MOM] What are
you doing, Yomogi? Let's go!

00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:15.602 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE TV HOST C] It's another
day in the life of this crazy

00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:16.686 position:50% align:center
big family.

00:07:16.770 --> 00:07:18.104 position:50% align:center
[KIDS shouting]

00:07:18.188 --> 00:07:19.397 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE TV HOST C ] The Hinode's
morning starts off...

00:07:19.481 --> 00:07:20.982 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
Thanks for the meal.

00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:26.654 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey. Can I go
into Kano's room?

00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:29.032 position:50% align:center
I wanna borrow something.

00:07:29.115 --> 00:07:30.575 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S MOM]
What?

00:07:30.658 --> 00:07:32.786 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
A book. It's for school.

00:07:32.869 --> 00:07:34.204 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S MOM]
That's fine.

00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.997 position:50% align:center
Just put it back
when you're done.

00:07:36.081 --> 00:07:37.457 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
'Kay.

00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:40.085 position:50% align:center
It's not like Kano's going
to need it anytime soon.

00:07:40.168 --> 00:07:41.795 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE TV MOM A ]
What have I said about running

00:07:41.878 --> 00:07:44.130 position:50% align:center
with knives in the house?

00:07:44.214 --> 00:07:45.507 position:50% align:center
--[YUME'S DAD chuckles] Huh?
--[YUME'S MOM] Honey!

00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:47.384 position:50% align:center
You left your plate
on the table again.

00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:49.427 position:50% align:center
[YUME gasps]
Here.

00:07:51.221 --> 00:07:52.639 position:50% align:center
[KANO]
Yume...

00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:58.978 position:50% align:center
[KANO]
Yume... I'd like you to come.

00:07:59.062 --> 00:08:00.563 position:50% align:center
Why, though?

00:08:02.107 --> 00:08:04.234 position:50% align:center
[clinking]

00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:06.069 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S DAD]
Speaking of cleaning...

00:08:06.152 --> 00:08:07.654 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S MOM]
What now?

00:08:07.737 --> 00:08:09.698 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S DAD] I think it's time
for you to clean something, too.

00:08:09.781 --> 00:08:10.990 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S MOM]
Which would be?

00:08:11.074 --> 00:08:13.034 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S DAD]
Kano's room. Enough is enough.

00:08:13.118 --> 00:08:14.160 position:50% align:center
[YUME sighs]

00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:16.371 position:50% align:center
[YUME'S MOM]
What do you want from me?

00:08:16.454 --> 00:08:17.622 position:50% align:center
[MALE REPORTER
A] According to police,

00:08:17.706 --> 00:08:19.624 position:50% align:center
the incident happened
at around 6 O'clock...

00:08:19.708 --> 00:08:23.503 position:50% align:center
Whoa. Hey, check out this
floating car on TV!

00:08:23.586 --> 00:08:25.255 position:50% align:center
[MALE INTERVIEWEE A] My garbage
can floated up in the air...

00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:27.924 position:50% align:center
Wake up, big guy!
Outta bed, sleepyhead!

00:08:28.008 --> 00:08:30.635 position:50% align:center
You're missing it!
Wakey, wakey, wakey!

00:08:33.388 --> 00:08:35.390 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI] And then the guy
grabbed me by the leg.

00:08:35.473 --> 00:08:37.517 position:50% align:center
[AWAKI sighs]
Whoa, weird.

00:08:37.600 --> 00:08:39.936 position:50% align:center
I was afraid he was
gonna eat me or something.

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:43.648 position:50% align:center
[GAUMA]
Yomogi! Hey!

00:08:43.732 --> 00:08:46.776 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Oh, no! Sorry you guys!

00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:50.071 position:50% align:center
--[NAZUMI] Huh?
--[AWAKI] Uh. Who's that?

00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:52.157 position:50% align:center
Looks like he's
having fun, huh?

00:08:57.037 --> 00:09:02.042 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI pants]

00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:15.430 position:50% align:center
Uh, hey.

00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:16.806 position:50% align:center
Yeah?

00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:19.809 position:50% align:center
Listen, would you happen
to have time after school?

00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:21.519 position:50% align:center
Today?

00:09:21.603 --> 00:09:22.562 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:24.397 position:50% align:center
Oh, uh...

00:09:24.481 --> 00:09:27.317 position:50% align:center
I'm Minami. Yume Minami.

00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:29.986 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I knew that.
We're in the same class.

00:09:30.070 --> 00:09:33.073 position:50% align:center
[YUME exhales]
Ah, right.

00:09:33.156 --> 00:09:36.034 position:50% align:center
So, I actually have work
after school today.

00:09:36.117 --> 00:09:37.327 position:50% align:center
Oh, I see.

00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:40.330 position:50% align:center
But, I think my shift
is over around eight.

00:09:40.413 --> 00:09:41.623 position:50% align:center
Then, in that case,

00:09:41.706 --> 00:09:43.917 position:50% align:center
can you please meet me
here around nine o'clock?

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.252 position:50% align:center
Sure thing, but for
what though?

00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:47.921 position:50% align:center
[YUME sighs]
Well...

00:09:48.004 --> 00:09:50.298 position:50% align:center
I just thought that if
anyone would hear me out,

00:09:50.382 --> 00:09:52.425 position:50% align:center
it would be you, Yomogi.

00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:58.682 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
You saw me here, right?

00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:00.266 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
Uh, yeah.

00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:02.769 position:50% align:center
[YUME] I take it you've heard
the rumors about me?

00:10:02.852 --> 00:10:04.604 position:50% align:center
[YOMOGI]
What? No.

00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:06.815 position:50% align:center
[YUME]
You don't have to pretend.

00:10:06.898 --> 00:10:10.402 position:50% align:center
Though, I feel like you
